section.section:
Each member of the State Board shall:
subject to subsection (g)(2) of this section, be appointed by the Governor in accordance with paragraph (2) of this subsection, with the advice and consent of the Senate of Maryland;
be a registered voter in the State for the 5 years immediately preceding the appointment;
subject to subsection (f)(3) of this section, be eligible for reappointment;
conform to the restrictions specified under § 2-301 of this title; and
be subject to removal by the Governor for incompetence, misconduct, or other good cause, upon written charges filed by the Governor with the State Board and after having been afforded notice and ample opportunity to be heard.
